How to Use Looker Studio for Your CitiBike Analytics

Quick Start Guide
Step 1: Access Looker Studio
Go to: https://lookerstudio.google.com/
Sign in with your Google account (same account that has access to your GCP project)
Step 2: Create a New Report
Click "Create" → "Report"
When prompted to add data, click "BigQuery"
Step 3: Connect to Your BigQuery Data
Select your project: nyc-citibike-data-platform
Select dataset: marts (your analytics-ready data)
Select table: Start with fct_trips or fct_station_day
Click "Add" → "Add to Report"
Step 4: Build Your First Dashboard
For Trip Analysis:

Data Source: marts.fct_trips
Dimensions: dim_date, dim_station, dim_user_type
Metrics: trip_count, avg_duration, total_revenue

txt


For Station Operations:

Data Source: marts.fct_station_day
Dimensions: station_name, date
Metrics: avg_bikes_available, total_trips_started, utilization_rate

